{"source_hash": "c53beff758d07130", "candidate": {"id": "cand-014", "name": "Oliver Prentice", "raw_cv": "OLIVER PRENTICE\noliver.prentice@email.com | Oxford, UK\n\nML ENGINEER\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nML engineer with 4 years of experience in NLP and classification systems, primarily in the legal tech and public sector space. Proficient in Python and PyTorch. Some exposure to government projects and compliance-sensitive environments.\n\nEXPERIENCE\n\nML Engineer \u2014 Luminance Technologies, London/Oxford (2021\u2013present)\n- Built and maintained NLP classification models for legal document review (M&A due diligence)\n- Led model evaluation framework using MLflow; reduced evaluation cycle time by 50%\n- Deployed ONNX-optimised models to production inference service\n- Worked with legal domain experts on training data annotation and model validation\n\nResearch Assistant \u2014 Oxford Internet Institute (2020\u20132021)\n- Developed text classification models for studying online misinformation patterns\n\nSKILLS\nPython, PyTorch, ONNX, MLflow, Hugging Face Transformers, scikit-learn, NumPy, Git, Docker\n\nEDUCATION\nMSc Statistics \u2014 University of Oxford (2019\u20132020)\nBSc Mathematics \u2014 University of Bath (2016\u20132019)\n\nRIGHT TO WORK\nBritish citizen", "raw_linkedin": "ML engineer working on NLP and document understanding systems at Luminance. Four years of experience applying transformers and classifiers to hard real-world problems where the output actually matters \u2014 legal document review. Good at the full stack from data curation to ONNX deployment. Based in Oxford. Interested in applied ML roles where the domain is interesting and the technical challenges are real. Open to defence, public sector, or legal tech.", "raw_interview_transcript": "Interviewer: Oliver, thanks for joining us. Your NLP background is interesting \u2014 how does it translate to perception and computer vision work?\n\nOliver: There's more overlap than you might think at the PyTorch level \u2014 the training infrastructure, experiment tracking, ONNX optimisation pipeline \u2014 it's largely the same. The core modelling knowledge is different, obviously, but I've been doing computer vision in my own time and I did some image classification work during my MSc. I'd be learning the sensor fusion aspects.\n\nInterviewer: The role does require strong computer vision fundamentals. Tell me about your experience with Cambridge \u2014 you're in Oxford currently?\n\nOliver: Yes, I'm in Oxford. Cambridge is fine \u2014 I'd probably get a place nearby or commute. The two days a week setup seems very manageable.\n\nInterviewer: And security clearance. Have you worked on any classified government projects?\n\nOliver: That's an interesting question. At Luminance we sometimes work with government legal teams on sensitive documents, and I've signed some additional NDAs and data handling agreements. I'm not sure exactly what that translates to in terms of formal clearance. I haven't been through a formal SC or DV vetting process, but I've handled sensitive information in a formal capacity. I think I'd be eligible for clearance \u2014 I'm UK national, no foreign ties \u2014 but I genuinely don't know if my past access counts for anything in the formal process.\n\nInterviewer: We can sponsor SC clearance. We'd just need you to be eligible. Salary?\n\nOliver: I'm at \u00a372,000. Looking for \u00a380\u201390,000 given the move and domain learning curve.", "years_experience": 4.0, "skills": ["Python", "PyTorch", "ONNX", "MLflow", "Hugging Face Transformers", "scikit-learn", "NumPy", "Git", "Docker", "NLP", "Text Classification", "Model Evaluation", "Computer Vision", "Image Classification", "Sensor Fusion", "Model Deployment"], "industries": ["Legal Tech", "Public Sector", "Defence"], "seniority_level": "mid", "management_experience": false, "education_level": "master", "career_trajectory": "ascending", "interview_score": 0.78, "culture_fit_score": 0.75, "constraints": [{"id": "f2753095", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Current salary \u00a372,000 (stated in interview)", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 72000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.98}, {"id": "305a6706", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Seeking minimum \u00a380,000 in new role", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 80000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.96}, {"id": "f23acfef", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Targeting salary range \u00a380\u201390,000", "canonical_key": "salary_max", "value": 90000.0, "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.92}, {"id": "a6fe77d4", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "location", "description": "Open to Cambridge role with 2 days per week onsite setup", "canonical_key": "office_days_per_week", "value": 2.0, "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.9}, {"id": "c1df123a", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "location", "description": "Currently based in Oxford; Cambridge acceptable with local arrangement", "canonical_key": "location_city", "value": "Oxford", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.94}, {"id": "066c71cf", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "visa", "description": "British citizen; no visa sponsorship required", "canonical_key": "visa_sponsorship", "value": false, "operator": "requires", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.98}, {"id": "f4afafdb", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "security", "description": "Eligible for SC clearance; no formal vetting yet but has handled sensitive government documents and signed NDAs", "canonical_key": "security_clearance", "value": "SC", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.85}, {"id": "3bf4c5ed", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "industry_background", "descri